{"build_type":"library","description":"Channel B real serve (v4, execve). Blocks on the request eventfd (fd3); copies the request out of the portal region; forks a child that dup2s an out memfd to stdout and EXECVEs the shell binary (shell_path passed in, a reliable source -- NOT the unreliable g_ld_libdir) with argv [shell_path, shell_path, request, 0] so the shell reads the request from argv[2] and resolves the pinned helper from argv[0]; the fresh process has its own loader so no nested resolve-closure and no libdir dependency. The parent reaps, reads the out memfd straight into the region, and rings the response eventfd (fd4). Output capture is a memfd, not a Linux pipe. Additive Channel B; does not touch Channel A.","module_name":"serve-portal-region-request-running-helper-writing-reply","package_name":"serve-portal-region-request-running-helper-writing-reply","function_definitions":{"serve-portal-region-request-running-helper-writing-reply":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"shell_path","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"unused1","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"three","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":3},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"four","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":4},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"eight","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":8},{"instruction_type"